Strength and Honor (I think a UK guild) did a long buff-festival just inside CB that was well received.<br>
<br>
We could run some newbie quests and contests. I have for a long time had some ideas on newbie quests and I am currently on tinkering sabbatical in steamfont, so RL pending, I should be there to spice things up. <br>
<br>
Is this a secure forum to discuss ideas? (I demand the cone of silence!) Let me know, I will share my devious plots later. Here are some fun events we can run that don't require secure communications, that add kind of a carnival atmosphere<br>
<br>
1) Platform Diving <br>
<br>
FP gathers a crowd at the bottom of a tall platform. A panel of judges is selected. Newbies are given UBER HP buffs at the top of the platform. Hassik hands them gnomish fireworks if they want. They each jump off the platform and perform whatever stunts they can before hitting the ground. FP members have hot keys that shout &quot;OOH. AHHH&quot;  A designated FP commentator rattles off the sports cliches: &quot;Ooh Zantor really stuck the landing on that one&quot;  &quot;wow! a half pike while firing off all 4 fireworks...unprecedented in competition diving&quot;<br>
or &quot;Ouch that's gonna hurt in the morning&quot;. The judges ooc their scores with added commentary. &quot;Heleth, I really like what bazuk did with his fireworks detonations, but I'm gonna have to deduct 2 tenths of a point for splattering on impact, 5.6&quot; (hopefully we will calibrate that noone dies)<br>
When they land, they are healed/rebuffed and winners are given prizes.<br>
<br>
Alternatively this event could be named Heleth's Wild Ride<br>
<br>
2) treetop races.<br>
<br>
contestants meet on one end of kelethin. they each get uber buffs. they each challenge a FP member to a duel (can u duel more than one person at a time)  That FP member casts some kind of blinding effect on them.<br>
With the help of a teammate barking out directions, each contestant, without casting spells, tries to run from one end of kelethin to the other.   <br>
<br>
Winning teams get prizes<br>
<br>
3) Get the Eye<br>
<br>
I believe that you can kill a PCs eye of zomm in a duel. If many people can duel one, they could all cahse and try to blast the eye as it runs about the treetops.<br>
<br>
4) Bonk Heleth<br>
<br>
I think there are lots of fun possibilties with contests where the first person to bonk a FPer wins. Heleth for example has a wide variety tactics available to disguise/hide/move about. Possibly, a bank of FPers can stand at the bank and offer whatever spells the contestants want (eg see invisible) to Find Heleth, who will not be allowed to leave the trees. <br>
<br>
